        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 8:54PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 854 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Grove Hill, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jackson and Grove Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
